properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 10 at 6:50PM CST until January 12 at 12:00AM CST by NWS La Crosse WI
properties.description:
...Accumulating Snow Tonight and Again Saturday...

.Periods of snow will continue across southwest Wisconsin into
portions of northeast Iowa this evening, tapering off quickly
after midnight. Snowfall amounts of 1 to locally 5 inches are
expected, highest across Grant County, Wisconsin.

After a short break Saturday morning, a second round of
accumulating snow is expected from Saturday afternoon into
Saturday night, with an additional 1 to locally 4 inches of
accumulation over parts of southwest into central Wisconsin. This
will bring total snow accumulations from tonight through Saturday
night of 2 to 8 inches.

If you will be driving tonight or the weekend, please stay up to
date on the latest road information and be prepared for wintry
travel conditions.

* WHAT...Periods of snow tonight, with a light accumulation.
Additional snow developing Saturday afternoon and evening, with
accumulation up to 3 inches.

* WHERE...Juneau and Adams Counties.

* WHEN...From 3 PM Saturday to midnight CST Saturday night.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. Patchy blowing
snow could reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 3 PM SATURDAY TO MIDNIGHT CST SATURDAY NIGHT
